1
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:11,666
Narrator: HEAVENS ARENA.

2
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:14,900
THE 251‐STORY BUILDING

3
00:00:14,900 --> 00:00:17,966
WHICH STANDS 991 METERS TALL

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,566
‐ IS A MECCA FOR FIGHTERS.
‐ ( crowd cheering )

5
00:00:20,566 --> 00:00:24,566
WHEN COMBATANTS WIN A FIGHT,
THEY MAY ADVANCE BY ONE CLASS

6
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:27,066
AND RECEIVE
A CORRESPONDING REWARD.

7
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:28,800
AFTER REACHING THE 100th FLOOR,

8
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:31,166
THEY ARE ASSIGNED
A PRIVATE ROOM.

9
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:34,566
AND THOSE CONTESTANTS WHO ARE
SKILLED AND FORTUNATE ENOUGH

10
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:36,300
TO REACH THE 200th FLOOR

11
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:39,600
EARN THE RIGHT TO CHALLENGE
THE STRONGEST FIGHTERS,

12
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:43,733
THE FLOOR MASTERS, IN AN INTENSE
BATTLE FOR SURVIVAL.

13
00:00:43,766 --> 00:00:46,300
THIS IS, WITHOUT A DOUBT,

14
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:49,433
THE BEST STAGE
A WARRIOR COULD ASK FOR.

15
00:00:51,766 --> 00:00:53,733
♪

16
00:00:57,266 --> 00:01:00,240
( singing in Japanese )

17
00:02:16,677 --> 00:02:20,410
Wing: YOU SAY THAT YOUR BROTHER
IS ABLE TO USE NEN?

18
00:02:20,443 --> 00:02:24,677
Killua: I NEED TO UNDERSTAND
WHAT NEN AND REN EVEN MEAN,

19
00:02:24,743 --> 00:02:26,910
AND NOT JUST HALFWAY.

20
00:02:26,943 --> 00:02:29,010
I NEED TO KNOW IT.

21
00:02:31,110 --> 00:02:33,510
Wing: WELL, IN THAT CASE...

22
00:02:33,510 --> 00:02:35,477
♪

23
00:02:38,343 --> 00:02:40,977
Narrator:
AFTER KILLUA FOUGHT ZUSHI,

24
00:02:41,010 --> 00:02:44,310
THE YOUNG PRACTITIONER
OF SHINGEN‐RYU MARTIAL ARTS,

25
00:02:44,343 --> 00:02:47,843
ZUSHI MENTIONED
THE FOUR EXERCISES.

26
00:02:47,910 --> 00:02:50,177
GON AND KILLUA
ARE ABOUT TO LEARN

27
00:02:50,177 --> 00:02:54,143
THE SECRET OF THOSE PRINCIPLES
FROM ZUSHI'S MASTER, WING.

28
00:02:54,177 --> 00:02:55,943
♪

29
00:02:55,977 --> 00:02:57,243
Wing: PAYING ATTENTION?

30
00:02:57,277 --> 00:03:01,317
NEN, OR FLAME,
IS A POWER THAT FIRES OUR SOULS.

31
00:03:01,350 --> 00:03:02,517
( marker squeaking )

32
00:03:02,517 --> 00:03:06,617
IN OTHER WORDS,
IT'S THE STRENGTH OF YOUR WILL.

33
00:03:06,650 --> 00:03:09,183
AND THE FOUR EXERCISES

34
00:03:09,183 --> 00:03:12,017
IS A TRAINING REGIMEN
THAT STRENGTHENS YOUR WILL.

35
00:03:12,017 --> 00:03:13,950
Gon: STRENGTHENS YOUR WILL?

36
00:03:13,983 --> 00:03:15,183
Killua: TRAINING?

37
00:03:15,183 --> 00:03:16,917
‐ ( marker squeaks )
‐ Wing: CORRECT.

38
00:03:16,950 --> 00:03:20,483
TEN, FOCUS THE MIND
ON A SINGLE POINT,

39
00:03:20,517 --> 00:03:23,083
REFLECT ON THE SELF,
AND DETERMINE THE GOAL.

40
00:03:23,117 --> 00:03:25,850
ZETSU, TO PUT INTO WORDS.

41
00:03:25,917 --> 00:03:28,817
REN IS TO INTENSIFY YOUR WILL.

42
00:03:28,850 --> 00:03:31,850
HATSU IS TO RELEASE IT
INTO ACTION.

43
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:35,850
Gon: TEN, ZETSU, REN, HATSU.

44
00:03:35,917 --> 00:03:38,183
THE FOUR EXERCISES.

45
00:03:38,250 --> 00:03:40,850
Wing: SEE, ZUSHI TEMPERED
HIS REFUSAL TO LOSE

46
00:03:40,917 --> 00:03:42,817
DURING HIS BATTLE
WITH YOU, KILLUA.

47
00:03:42,850 --> 00:03:44,950
( Killua grunts )

48
00:03:47,850 --> 00:03:49,950
( gasps )

49
00:03:52,817 --> 00:03:55,250
Wing: NOW ALLOW ME
TO DEMONSTRATE.

50
00:03:55,283 --> 00:03:57,117
‐ KILLUA...
‐ Killua: EH?

51
00:03:57,150 --> 00:04:00,617
Wing: FOR THIS DEMONSTRATION,
I WOULD LIKE TO "KILL" YOU NOW.

52
00:04:00,650 --> 00:04:01,857
IS THAT ALL RIGHT?

53
00:04:01,857 --> 00:04:03,090
Killua: SURE. WHY NOT?

54
00:04:03,123 --> 00:04:04,957
BUT YOU WON'T BE ABLE TO.

55
00:04:05,857 --> 00:04:07,623
Wing: LET'S DO THIS IN ORDER.

56
00:04:07,657 --> 00:04:09,523
FIRST, TEN.

57
00:04:11,090 --> 00:04:13,990
I FOCUS MY MIND
ON A SINGLE POINT.

58
00:04:15,023 --> 00:04:18,823
ZETSU,
EXPRESS YOUR DESIRED INTENT

59
00:04:18,857 --> 00:04:21,157
EITHER MENTALLY OR VERBALLY.

60
00:04:24,690 --> 00:04:26,623
I WILL KILL YOU.

61
00:04:26,657 --> 00:04:28,523
♪

62
00:04:29,623 --> 00:04:30,523
( both gasp )

63
00:04:43,457 --> 00:04:45,423
( Gon gasps )

64
00:04:45,457 --> 00:04:47,357
( Killua gasping )

65
00:05:08,830 --> 00:05:10,163
Wing: THAT WAS A TASTE OF REN.

66
00:05:10,197 --> 00:05:12,997
WITH ENOUGH STRENGTH AND FOCUS,

67
00:05:13,030 --> 00:05:16,163
THE WILL FUNCTIONS
AS ACTION, OR HATSU.

68
00:05:17,030 --> 00:05:18,530
WITH A STRONG WILL,

69
00:05:18,597 --> 00:05:20,797
YOUR OPPONENT WILL BACK DOWN.

70
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:23,863
A MORE FAMILIAR TERM
WOULD BE BLUFFING.

71
00:05:25,030 --> 00:05:27,430
REN HARDENS THAT WHICH IS SOFT,

72
00:05:27,463 --> 00:05:28,830
AND YOU SUDDENLY FIND

73
00:05:28,863 --> 00:05:32,197
THAT YOU'VE LOST YOUR ABILITY
TO CORRECT AN INCORRECT IDEA.

74
00:05:32,263 --> 00:05:35,030
THEREFORE, UNTIL YOUR SOUL
HAS FULLY MATURED,

75
00:05:35,030 --> 00:05:36,697
AVOID USING REN.

76
00:05:36,697 --> 00:05:38,197
AS IT STANDS NOW,

77
00:05:38,197 --> 00:05:41,830
YOU THREE BOYS SHOULD REALLY
FOCUS ON TRAINING YOUR SOULS.

78
00:05:45,697 --> 00:05:46,830
( Killua sighs )

79
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:49,263
LET'S GO, GON.

80
00:05:49,297 --> 00:05:52,197
Wing: IF YOU TRULY WISH
TO LEARN ABOUT NEN,

81
00:05:52,197 --> 00:05:54,697
SET YOUR SIGHTS
ON MASTERING TEN FIRST.

82
00:05:54,763 --> 00:05:56,697
IF YOU MASTER TEN,

83
00:05:56,697 --> 00:06:00,337
YOU NO LONGER FEEL THE PRESSURE
OF AN OPPONENT'S WILL.

84
00:06:04,503 --> 00:06:06,270
Gon: THANK YOU VERY MUCH!

85
00:06:10,837 --> 00:06:13,303
WAIT UP, KILLUA!

86
00:06:13,337 --> 00:06:14,303
( Wing sighs )

87
00:06:14,337 --> 00:06:15,770
ZUSHI.

88
00:06:15,803 --> 00:06:16,970
Zushi: YES, SIR?

89
00:06:17,003 --> 00:06:18,703
Wing: LET'S BEGIN YOUR TRAINING.

90
00:06:18,703 --> 00:06:20,037
Zushi: OSU!

91
00:06:20,870 --> 00:06:22,870
Wing: FIRST OFF...

92
00:06:26,637 --> 00:06:27,703
Gon: HE LIED?

93
00:06:27,703 --> 00:06:28,970
Killua: YEAH.

94
00:06:29,003 --> 00:06:31,270
WHAT HE SAID WAS TRUE,
FAR AS IT WENT,

95
00:06:31,303 --> 00:06:33,503
AND HIS POWER
IS THE REAL DEAL, TOO,

96
00:06:33,537 --> 00:06:36,370
BUT THERE ARE A FEW THINGS
IT DOESN'T COVER.

97
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:37,203
Gon: LIKE?

98
00:06:37,203 --> 00:06:39,503
Killua: LIKE HOW TOUGH ZUSHI IS.

99
00:06:39,537 --> 00:06:43,703
IN OUR FIGHT, HE GOT UP
EVERY TIME I KNOCKED HIM DOWN.

100
00:06:43,703 --> 00:06:45,203
THAT WAS PRETTY ANNOYING,

101
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:48,703
WHICH IS WHY I GOT A LITTLE
PUSHY WITH HIM AT THE END.

102
00:06:48,703 --> 00:06:49,703
( Gon gasps )

103
00:06:49,703 --> 00:06:51,637
( crowd cheering )

104
00:06:51,670 --> 00:06:53,703
( Zushi panting )

105
00:06:53,703 --> 00:06:55,870
♪

106
00:06:58,703 --> 00:07:00,877
( Killua gasps )
WHY, YOU...

107
00:07:07,377 --> 00:07:08,377
( Zushi gags )

108
00:07:08,377 --> 00:07:10,377
( Killua gasps )

109
00:07:10,443 --> 00:07:11,510
OOPS.

110
00:07:14,343 --> 00:07:17,877
Cocco: OHH!
ZUSHI SAILS OUT OF THE RING!

111
00:07:17,943 --> 00:07:20,543
AND STRAIGHT TO THE HOSPITAL,
BY THE LOOKS OF IT.

112
00:07:20,543 --> 00:07:21,810
THAT'S GOTTA HURT!

113
00:07:21,843 --> 00:07:23,610
( crowd cheering )

114
00:07:23,643 --> 00:07:25,143
( Killua gasps )

115
00:07:28,043 --> 00:07:30,543
Cocco: HE'S GOTTEN
BACK UP, FOLKS.

116
00:07:30,543 --> 00:07:32,710
ZUSHI MUST BE INVINCIBLE!

117
00:07:32,777 --> 00:07:34,143
( Zushi panting )

118
00:07:35,710 --> 00:07:37,377
Killua: NO WAY.

119
00:07:37,443 --> 00:07:39,610
Cocco: BUT THE REFEREE
HAS AWARDED

120
00:07:39,643 --> 00:07:41,310
A CRITICAL HIT AND KNOCKDOWN.

121
00:07:41,343 --> 00:07:45,543
KILLUA WINS BY T. K. O.
WITH 11 TOTAL POINTS.

122
00:07:45,543 --> 00:07:48,310
( crowd cheering )

123
00:07:48,343 --> 00:07:50,443
Killua: IT WASN'T
HIS STRENGTH OF WILL ALONE

124
00:07:50,477 --> 00:07:52,443
THAT KEPT HIM STANDING
THAT WHOLE TIME.

125
00:07:52,477 --> 00:07:54,877
THERE'S GOTTA BE
SOMETHING ELSE HE'S HIDING.

126
00:07:54,943 --> 00:07:57,110
Gon: HMM.

127
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:59,043
♪

128
00:08:00,377 --> 00:08:02,117
Wing: WHAT'S THE MATTER, ZUSHI?

129
00:08:02,150 --> 00:08:05,117
YOUR TEN IS AGGRAVATED.

130
00:08:06,317 --> 00:08:08,317
‐ Zushi: MASTER...
‐ Wing: HMM?

131
00:08:08,350 --> 00:08:12,517
Zushi: WHY DID YOU LIE
TO GON AND KILLUA JUST NOW?

132
00:08:12,550 --> 00:08:14,283
Wing: LIE?

133
00:08:14,317 --> 00:08:16,650
ARE YOU REFERRING
TO MY EXPLANATION?

134
00:08:16,683 --> 00:08:18,017
Zushi: YES.

135
00:08:18,050 --> 00:08:21,550
THE FOUR EXERCISES ARE
TEN, ZETSU, REN, AND HATSU,

136
00:08:21,617 --> 00:08:24,017
BUT THEY DON'T MEAN
WHAT YOU TOLD THEM.

137
00:08:24,050 --> 00:08:25,883
DID YOU DECIDE TO LIE TO THEM

138
00:08:25,950 --> 00:08:27,350
BECAUSE THEY AREN'T
YOUR STUDENTS?

139
00:08:28,983 --> 00:08:30,383
Wing: I DIDN'T LIE.

140
00:08:30,383 --> 00:08:32,783
THAT NEN IS
AN IMPORTANT DISCIPLINE

141
00:08:32,817 --> 00:08:34,950
IN TRAINING THE MIND...

142
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:39,283
FOR THIS NEN.

143
00:08:41,483 --> 00:08:43,617
HOWEVER, IT'S TRUE

144
00:08:43,650 --> 00:08:47,117
THAT I CANNOT TEACH NEN
TO SOMEONE WHO IS NOT A STUDENT,

145
00:08:47,150 --> 00:08:49,550
SO I USED THE OTHER NEN
AS A HINT

146
00:08:49,617 --> 00:08:50,950
JUST TO HELP THEM ALONG.

147
00:08:50,983 --> 00:08:53,883
IF THE NEN I TEACH
IS USED IN THE WRONG WAY,

148
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:57,317
IT CAN BECOME
A TERRIBLE WEAPON, ZUSHI.

149
00:08:57,350 --> 00:08:58,817
( page flutters )

150
00:08:58,850 --> 00:09:01,223
‐ FOR EXAMPLE...
‐ ( rip )

151
00:09:08,390 --> 00:09:09,390
Zushi: HUH?

152
00:09:28,190 --> 00:09:30,890
Wing: YOU COULD TURN
A SIMPLE PIECE OF PAPER

153
00:09:30,890 --> 00:09:32,723
INTO QUITE A HARMFUL BLADE.

154
00:09:32,723 --> 00:09:34,823
FURTHERMORE,
YOU COULD HARDEN YOUR BODY

155
00:09:34,857 --> 00:09:36,557
AS A DEFENSIVE MEASURE.

156
00:09:38,190 --> 00:09:42,123
WITH ENOUGH WORK,
ANYONE CAN USE NEN,

157
00:09:42,157 --> 00:09:44,857
WHICH IS WHY
YOU MUST BE VERY CAREFUL

158
00:09:44,890 --> 00:09:47,357
WHEN CHOOSING
WHO TO TEACH IT TO.

159
00:09:48,790 --> 00:09:52,157
Zushi: MASTER, IT'S JUST...

160
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:55,957
THAT I HADN'T GOTTEN THE CHANCE
TO READ THAT BOOK YET.

161
00:09:55,990 --> 00:09:56,990
( Wing gasps )

162
00:09:57,023 --> 00:09:58,457
Zushi: AND THAT JUICE...

163
00:09:58,490 --> 00:09:59,623
IT WAS MINE.

164
00:09:59,657 --> 00:10:00,563
( Wing stammers )

165
00:10:00,597 --> 00:10:02,230
I'M SORRY!

166
00:10:02,263 --> 00:10:04,163
♪

167
00:10:07,330 --> 00:10:09,330
( crowd cheering )

168
00:10:09,397 --> 00:10:13,130
Cocco: IT'S TIME FOR
THE BIGGEST MATCH OF THE DAY!

169
00:10:13,163 --> 00:10:15,997
TWO ROOKIES HAVE ADVANCED
TO THE 190th FLOOR

170
00:10:15,997 --> 00:10:18,397
WITHOUT LOSING A SINGLE FIGHT,

171
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:20,763
GON AND KILLUA!

172
00:10:20,797 --> 00:10:25,097
WILL THEY BE ABLE TO CLEAR
TODAY'S MATCH IN ONE SHOT, TOO?

173
00:10:25,997 --> 00:10:27,663
OKAY, EVERYONE,

174
00:10:27,730 --> 00:10:30,497
GET READY TO PRESS
YOUR WAGER BUTTONS!

175
00:10:32,663 --> 00:10:34,097
( fighter scoffs )

176
00:10:34,130 --> 00:10:35,997
UNFORTUNATELY FOR YOU,

177
00:10:35,997 --> 00:10:39,263
THAT LITTLE PUSH MOVE OF YOURS
WON'T WORK ON ME.

178
00:10:39,297 --> 00:10:42,763
THAT'S BECAUSE
I'M AS SLIPPERY AS A SNAKE,

179
00:10:42,797 --> 00:10:44,997
AND MY FANGS ARE JUST AS SHARP,

180
00:10:45,063 --> 00:10:49,163
FANGS THAT ARE JUST DYING FOR
A TASTE OF YOUR VITAL POINTS.

181
00:10:51,097 --> 00:10:53,163
( fighter #2 laughs )

182
00:10:53,230 --> 00:10:55,463
YOU MIGHT SPORT
A VICIOUS CHOP, KID,

183
00:10:55,497 --> 00:10:59,463
BUT IT WON'T BE ENOUGH
TO SAVE YOU FROM THESE MUSCLES!

184
00:10:59,497 --> 00:11:01,470
AND DO YOU WANNA KNOW WHY?

185
00:11:01,503 --> 00:11:02,503
( grunts )

186
00:11:02,503 --> 00:11:05,003
BECAUSE I'M TOTALLY RIPPED,
OBVIOUSLY!

187
00:11:06,337 --> 00:11:07,837
( Killua sighs )

188
00:11:07,903 --> 00:11:09,670
Referee: AND BEGIN!

189
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:11,837
Fighter #1: Hee‐yah!

190
00:11:11,837 --> 00:11:14,137
( fighter #2 yells )

191
00:11:16,003 --> 00:11:18,170
( crowd cheering )

192
00:11:23,557 --> 00:11:25,657
( crowd cheering )

193
00:11:31,681 --> 00:11:33,748
Referee #2:
THAT'S A CRITICAL HIT

194
00:11:33,781 --> 00:11:34,948
AND KNOCKDOWN!

195
00:11:35,015 --> 00:11:36,515
THAT'S THREE POINTS!

196
00:11:36,548 --> 00:11:37,515
IT'S A KNOCKOUT!

197
00:11:37,548 --> 00:11:41,015
AND WINNER IS GON!

198
00:11:43,515 --> 00:11:45,548
Referee #1:
CRITICAL HIT AND KNOCKDOWN!

199
00:11:45,581 --> 00:11:46,581
THAT'S THREE POINTS!

200
00:11:46,615 --> 00:11:49,381
KNOCKOUT! KILLUA WINS!

201
00:11:49,415 --> 00:11:52,781
( crowd cheering )

202
00:11:52,848 --> 00:11:54,548
Cocco: ONCE AGAIN,
GON AND KILLUA

203
00:11:54,581 --> 00:11:57,448
HAVE KNOCKED OUT THEIR OPPONENTS
WITH ONE ATTACK,

204
00:11:57,515 --> 00:11:58,881
MEANING BOTH OF THEM

205
00:11:58,915 --> 00:12:02,888
HAVE SUCCESSFULLY CLEARED
THE 190th FLOOR!

206
00:12:02,921 --> 00:12:06,521
BOTH COMPETITORS ADVANCE
TO THE 200th FLOOR!

207
00:12:06,555 --> 00:12:09,221
Zushi: THE 200th FLOOR ALREADY?!

208
00:12:09,255 --> 00:12:10,888
Wing: ZUSHI.

209
00:12:10,921 --> 00:12:12,455
Zushi: MASTER WING.

210
00:12:12,521 --> 00:12:15,021
Wing: KILLUA AND GON
HAVE ALREADY REACHED

211
00:12:15,055 --> 00:12:17,021
THE 200th FLOOR, HAVE THEY?

212
00:12:17,021 --> 00:12:20,521
Zushi: YES!
THEY'RE BOTH AMAZING FIGHTERS.

213
00:12:20,521 --> 00:12:22,055
I REALLY NEED TO TRAIN M‐‐

214
00:12:22,088 --> 00:12:25,921
UH, WHAT THE? MASTER?

215
00:12:35,355 --> 00:12:38,288
Wing: I GUESS
I DON'T HAVE A CHOICE.

216
00:12:38,355 --> 00:12:39,521
Guide: ENJOY.

217
00:12:47,121 --> 00:12:49,021
Gon: THE 200th FLOOR.

218
00:12:49,021 --> 00:12:50,255
SO WHAT'S IT LIKE?

219
00:12:50,288 --> 00:12:53,121
Killua: BEATS ME.
NEVER ACTUALLY BEEN THERE.

220
00:12:53,188 --> 00:12:55,588
BUT I GUESS
WE'RE GONNA FIND OUT.

221
00:12:55,621 --> 00:12:57,555
♪

222
00:12:59,221 --> 00:13:01,295
( ding )

223
00:13:07,595 --> 00:13:09,228
Gon: WOW!

224
00:13:09,261 --> 00:13:12,195
THE 200th FLOOR
SURE IS FANCY, HUH?

225
00:13:12,228 --> 00:13:13,528
Killua: WHERE'S RECEPTION?

226
00:13:14,728 --> 00:13:16,028
MAYBE THIS WAY.

227
00:13:20,195 --> 00:13:22,228
Gon: WE FINALLY MADE IT.

228
00:13:22,261 --> 00:13:23,361
Killua: YEAH.

229
00:13:29,361 --> 00:13:30,528
( both gasp )

230
00:13:30,528 --> 00:13:32,461
♪

231
00:13:38,528 --> 00:13:40,195
Gon: WHAT IS THIS?

232
00:13:40,228 --> 00:13:44,295
IT SUDDENLY FEELS LIKE WE'RE IN
A JUNGLE SWARMING WITH MONSTERS,

233
00:13:44,361 --> 00:13:48,095
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE
AN ORDINARY HALLWAY.

234
00:13:56,061 --> 00:13:59,095
Killua: LET'S GO.
WE CAN DO THIS.

235
00:14:18,035 --> 00:14:19,768
Gon: IT'S NOT WORKING.

236
00:14:19,801 --> 00:14:22,701
I CAN'T GO ON!
I DON'T WANT TO!

237
00:14:22,701 --> 00:14:24,535
DO YOU FEEL THAT BLOODLUST?

238
00:14:24,535 --> 00:14:26,968
IT'S DIRECTED RIGHT AT US!

239
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:31,535
Killua: OKAY, THAT'S ENOUGH!
WHO'S THERE?!

240
00:14:31,535 --> 00:14:33,035
SHOW YOURSELF!

241
00:14:35,935 --> 00:14:37,301
( receptionist chuckles )

242
00:14:37,368 --> 00:14:39,701
♪

243
00:14:39,735 --> 00:14:42,101
YOU MUST BE KILLUA AND GON.

244
00:14:42,135 --> 00:14:44,401
THE RECEPTION DESK IS THIS WAY,

245
00:14:44,435 --> 00:14:49,201
SO PLEASE REGISTER
FOR A 200th‐FLOOR MATCH TODAY.

246
00:14:49,235 --> 00:14:52,201
BE ADVISED THAT YOUR ELIGIBILITY
FOR THIS FLOOR

247
00:14:52,201 --> 00:14:55,535
EXPIRES AT MIDNIGHT,
SO PLEASE DON'T DELAY.

248
00:14:56,701 --> 00:14:59,701
Gon: DID THAT FEELING
COME FROM HER?

249
00:14:59,701 --> 00:15:01,035
Killua: I CAN'T TELL.

250
00:15:01,035 --> 00:15:04,208
Receptionist: BY THE WAY,
ON THE 200th FLOOR,

251
00:15:04,208 --> 00:15:08,708
THERE ARE CURRENTLY
173 CONTESTANTS.

252
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:10,808
AND FROM THIS FLOOR UP,

253
00:15:10,875 --> 00:15:13,208
ALL WEAPONS ARE ALLOWED
IN ALL MATCHES,

254
00:15:13,241 --> 00:15:16,208
SO PLEASE FEEL FREE
TO USE WHATEVER YOU HAVE.

255
00:15:16,241 --> 00:15:19,241
ALSO, AS OF THE 200th FLOOR,

256
00:15:19,275 --> 00:15:21,708
YOU WILL NO LONGER RECEIVE
PRIZE MONEY.

257
00:15:21,741 --> 00:15:24,541
NOW YOU WILL BE FIGHTING
ONLY FOR HONOR.

258
00:15:24,541 --> 00:15:27,541
PLEASE KEEP THAT IN MIND
IF YOU PARTICIPATE.

259
00:15:27,541 --> 00:15:28,541
( both gasp )

260
00:15:28,541 --> 00:15:29,475
( receptionist gasps )

261
00:15:37,875 --> 00:15:40,041
( receptionist gasps )

262
00:15:50,308 --> 00:15:52,208
Killua: H‐HISOKA.

263
00:15:52,208 --> 00:15:54,208
BUT WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

264
00:15:54,241 --> 00:15:57,475
Hisoka: IT ISN'T
THAT STRANGE, IS IT?

265
00:15:57,541 --> 00:16:03,048
I LOVE TO FIGHT, AND THIS IS
A TEMPLE DEVOTED TO THE CRAFT.

266
00:16:03,048 --> 00:16:07,548
THE REAL QUESTION IS,
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

267
00:16:07,548 --> 00:16:09,715
JUST KIDDING.

268
00:16:09,715 --> 00:16:12,548
THIS MEETING IS
NO MERE COINCIDENCE.

269
00:16:12,581 --> 00:16:14,081
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR YOU.

270
00:16:14,115 --> 00:16:16,081
REMEMBER HOW YOU
ORDERED YOUR TICKETS

271
00:16:16,115 --> 00:16:18,248
FOR THE AIRSHIP
OVER THE INTERNET?

272
00:16:19,315 --> 00:16:22,048
WITH ONLY A LITTLE EFFORT
ON MY PART,

273
00:16:22,048 --> 00:16:26,548
I WAS ABLE TO FIND OUT
EXACTLY WHEN YOU WOULD ARRIVE.

274
00:16:26,548 --> 00:16:31,048
WELL, IN ANY CASE, I KNEW
YOU WOULD COME HERE EVENTUALLY.

275
00:16:31,948 --> 00:16:34,448
AND SO AS YOUR SENIOR,

276
00:16:34,481 --> 00:16:38,548
I HAVE A LITTLE BIT OF
A WARNING FOR THE BOTH OF YOU.

277
00:16:38,548 --> 00:16:40,081
( both grunt )

278
00:16:40,115 --> 00:16:43,548
Hisoka: YOU'RE STILL NOT READY
TO SET FOOT ON THIS FLOOR...

279
00:16:44,981 --> 00:16:47,081
NOT BY A LONG SHOT.

280
00:16:48,148 --> 00:16:50,981
‐ ( force strikes )
‐ ( both grunting )

281
00:16:52,315 --> 00:16:56,048
Hisoka: WHEN YOU WILL BE
DEPENDS ON YOUR EFFORTS.

282
00:16:56,081 --> 00:16:59,548
FOR NOW, LEAVE THIS FLOOR.

283
00:16:59,548 --> 00:17:00,888
IT'S FAR TOO EARLY.

284
00:17:00,888 --> 00:17:01,888
Killua: WAIT. WHAT?!

285
00:17:01,888 --> 00:17:02,888
THAT'S STUPID!

286
00:17:02,888 --> 00:17:05,088
WE JUST GOT UP HERE!

287
00:17:07,588 --> 00:17:10,421
I WON'T LET YOU PASS,

288
00:17:10,455 --> 00:17:13,888
BUT IT'S NOT LIKE
YOU COULD, ANYWAY.

289
00:17:14,888 --> 00:17:17,421
( Killua groans )
WHAT THE HELL?!

290
00:17:17,455 --> 00:17:19,888
Gon: WHAT IS THIS?

291
00:17:27,088 --> 00:17:29,821
Man: DON'T BE RECKLESS.

292
00:17:29,888 --> 00:17:31,055
( footsteps )

293
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:36,721
Gon: MR. WING!

294
00:17:36,755 --> 00:17:38,721
Wing: WHAT HE'S SAYING IS TRUE.

295
00:17:38,755 --> 00:17:40,788
YOU HAVE NO DEFENSE
AGAINST HIS NEN.

296
00:17:40,821 --> 00:17:42,221
Gon: NEN?

297
00:17:42,255 --> 00:17:45,888
Wing: AS IT STANDS, YOU ARE
BOTH NAKED IN A BLIZZARD,

298
00:17:45,921 --> 00:17:48,555
BOTH OF YOU WONDERING
WHY IT'S SO COLD.

299
00:17:48,588 --> 00:17:52,721
IF YOU CONTINUE TO STRAIN
YOUR BODIES, YOU MAY DIE.

300
00:17:52,755 --> 00:17:54,421
Killua: SO THIS IS NEN?

301
00:17:54,455 --> 00:17:57,921
HE CAN STOP US FROM MOVING
FORWARD THROUGH WILLPOWER?

302
00:17:57,955 --> 00:17:59,588
YOU LIAR!

303
00:17:59,621 --> 00:18:01,561
Wing: YES, I WAS LYING.

304
00:18:01,561 --> 00:18:02,961
( both gasp )

305
00:18:02,995 --> 00:18:06,228
Wing: THOUGH SOME OF WHAT I SAID
WAS TECHNICALLY TRUE.

306
00:18:06,261 --> 00:18:08,961
I WILL TEACH YOU
THE TRUTH ABOUT NEN,

307
00:18:08,995 --> 00:18:12,161
SO FOR THE TIME BEING,
I SUGGEST WE WITHDRAW.

308
00:18:13,995 --> 00:18:15,428
Gon: UH, 'SCUSE ME.

309
00:18:15,461 --> 00:18:16,561
Receptionist: OH. YES?

310
00:18:16,595 --> 00:18:19,495
Gon: IF WE DON'T REGISTER
FOR A FIGHT TODAY,

311
00:18:19,561 --> 00:18:21,061
HOW WOULD THAT AFFECT US?

312
00:18:21,061 --> 00:18:24,395
Receptionist: WELL, YOU WOULD
HAVE TO START ALL OVER AGAIN

313
00:18:24,428 --> 00:18:25,928
FROM THE FIRST FLOOR.

314
00:18:25,961 --> 00:18:27,328
KILLUA, HOWEVER,

315
00:18:27,395 --> 00:18:31,128
HE'S BEEN HERE BEFORE
AND REFUSED TO REGISTER.

316
00:18:31,161 --> 00:18:33,461
SO IF HE FAILS TO DO SO AGAIN,

317
00:18:33,495 --> 00:18:35,561
HIS COMMITMENT
WILL BE CALLED INTO QUESTION,

318
00:18:35,561 --> 00:18:38,561
AND HE WILL BE BANNED
FROM PARTICIPATING.

319
00:18:38,561 --> 00:18:40,461
( Killua groans )

320
00:18:41,895 --> 00:18:43,628
‐ MR. WING.
‐ Wing: HUH?

321
00:18:43,661 --> 00:18:45,628
Killua: IF WE WITHDRAW,

322
00:18:45,661 --> 00:18:49,395
WILL WE BE ABLE TO MAKE IT
BACK HERE BY MIDNIGHT?

323
00:18:51,228 --> 00:18:52,161
Gon: HMM.

324
00:18:55,661 --> 00:18:57,161
Hisoka: HMM.

325
00:18:58,061 --> 00:19:00,401
Wing: THAT ALL DEPENDS ON YOU.

326
00:19:02,668 --> 00:19:04,235
( beep )

327
00:19:07,101 --> 00:19:09,768
SIMPLY PUT, THIS IS NEN.

328
00:19:09,801 --> 00:19:12,235
( water trickling )

329
00:19:12,235 --> 00:19:16,001
NEN REFERS TO THE ABILITY
TO CONTROL YOUR AURA,

330
00:19:16,068 --> 00:19:20,235
WHICH, AS YOU MAY KNOW,
IS ALSO KNOWN AS LIFE ENERGY.

331
00:19:20,268 --> 00:19:24,735
EVERYONE IN THE WORLD HAS
A SMALL AMOUNT OF LIFE ENERGY,

332
00:19:24,768 --> 00:19:28,835
BUT IN MOST CASES,
IT SIMPLY LEAKS AWAY.

333
00:19:28,901 --> 00:19:32,901
THE ABILITY
TO BUILD UP AND CONTAIN

334
00:19:32,901 --> 00:19:35,668
THIS LIFE ENERGY
IS KNOWN AS TEN.

335
00:19:35,735 --> 00:19:39,268
USING TEN,
YOU CAN MAKE YOUR BODY TOUGHER

336
00:19:39,301 --> 00:19:42,735
AND CONSIDERABLY SLOW
THE EFFECTS OF AGING.

337
00:19:42,735 --> 00:19:44,301
THEN COMES ZETSU,

338
00:19:44,335 --> 00:19:47,435
WHICH SHUTS OFF
THE FLOW OF AURA.

339
00:19:47,468 --> 00:19:48,901
IT IS QUITE EFFECTIVE

340
00:19:48,901 --> 00:19:50,901
FOR CONCEALING
YOUR PRESENCE FROM OTHERS

341
00:19:50,935 --> 00:19:52,635
AND RECOVERING FROM FATIGUE.

342
00:19:52,668 --> 00:19:55,735
WHICH BRINGS US TO REN.

343
00:19:55,768 --> 00:19:58,901
IT ENABLES YOU
TO PRODUCE MORE AURA.

344
00:19:58,935 --> 00:20:00,068
( both gasp )

345
00:20:05,008 --> 00:20:06,875
Wing: CAN YOU FEEL THAT?

346
00:20:06,908 --> 00:20:10,008
Killua: YEAH.
IT'S LIKE PRESSURE.

347
00:20:10,008 --> 00:20:13,175
Gon: BUT IT DOESN'T FEEL
WEIRD OR CREEPY.

348
00:20:13,208 --> 00:20:17,175
Wing: THAT'S BECAUSE
I HAVE ABSOLUTELY NO MALICE.

349
00:20:17,175 --> 00:20:20,008
( thinking )
I MUST ADMIT I'M IMPRESSED.

350
00:20:20,008 --> 00:20:22,408
THEIR SENSES ARE AMAZING.

351
00:20:22,441 --> 00:20:24,175
PERHAPS IT'S A PRODUCT

352
00:20:24,175 --> 00:20:26,875
OF THE ENVIRONMENTS
IN WHICH THEY WERE RAISED,

353
00:20:26,908 --> 00:20:29,941
BUT THEIR INNATE GIFTS
ARE ALSO A FACTOR.

354
00:20:31,108 --> 00:20:34,275
AURA IS AN ENERGY
DWELLING WITHIN ALL HUMANS,

355
00:20:34,341 --> 00:20:38,508
WHICH MAKES IT VERY EFFECTIVE
AGAINST OTHER HUMANS,

356
00:20:38,508 --> 00:20:41,375
FOR BETTER OR FOR WORSE.

357
00:20:41,408 --> 00:20:45,508
IF YOU ATTACK A HELPLESS PERSON
WITH MALICE,

358
00:20:45,541 --> 00:20:49,008
YOU CAN KILL USING AURA ALONE.

359
00:20:51,675 --> 00:20:55,508
ONLY ONE THING CAN PROTECT YOU
FROM A USER OF NEN.

360
00:20:56,675 --> 00:20:59,008
YOU MUST LEARN
TO USE IT YOURSELF

361
00:20:59,008 --> 00:21:01,415
AND USE TEN FOR DEFENSE,

362
00:21:01,448 --> 00:21:05,248
BLOCK THE OTHER PERSON'S AURA
WITH YOUR OWN.

363
00:21:07,415 --> 00:21:08,548
OTHERWISE...

364
00:21:22,848 --> 00:21:25,015
( both gasp )

365
00:21:30,681 --> 00:21:34,115
YOUR BODY WILL BE SHATTERED
BEYOND ALL RECOGNITION.

366
00:21:36,181 --> 00:21:37,748
♪

367
00:21:37,781 --> 00:21:41,915
Narrator: HISOKA BLOCKS THE PATH
LEADING BEYOND THE 200th FLOOR.

368
00:21:41,948 --> 00:21:45,348
GON AND KILLUA
HAVE BEGUN THEIR STUDIES,

369
00:21:45,381 --> 00:21:48,681
BUT WILL THEY BE ABLE
TO LEARN ENOUGH ABOUT TRUE NEN

370
00:21:48,715 --> 00:21:50,781
TO PASS HISOKA
AND REACH THE RECEPTIONIST

371
00:21:50,848 --> 00:21:54,348
ALL BEFORE THE CLOCK
STRIKES MIDNIGHT?

372
00:21:56,015 --> 00:21:59,848
( Hisoka chuckles )

373
00:21:59,881 --> 00:22:01,288
NOT YET.

374
00:22:01,355 --> 00:22:03,021
IT'S TOO SOON.

375
00:22:03,021 --> 00:22:05,188
( singing in Japanese )

376
00:23:12,961 --> 00:23:14,861
Gon: COMING UP, GON...

377
00:23:14,861 --> 00:23:15,861
Killua: AND KILLUA'S...

378
00:23:15,895 --> 00:23:16,795
Both: HUNTERPEDIA!

379
00:23:20,204 --> 00:23:21,138
Gon: I'M GON.

380
00:23:21,204 --> 00:23:22,038
Killua: I'M KILLUA.

381
00:23:22,071 --> 00:23:23,538
Both: AND THIS IS
OUR HUNTERPEDIA!

382
00:23:23,538 --> 00:23:25,538
Gon: TODAY WE'LL
INTRODUCE MR. WING,

383
00:23:25,538 --> 00:23:27,771
ZUSHI'S MASTER
AND AN EXPERT AT SHINGEN‐RYU.

384
00:23:27,804 --> 00:23:30,204
Killua: IT SEEMS LIKE HE'S
PRETTY GOOD WITH NEN.

385
00:23:30,238 --> 00:23:32,038
Gon: OH, YEAH,
BUT ISN'T HIS SHIRT UNTUCKED?

386
00:23:32,071 --> 00:23:33,271
Killua: AND HE'S GOT BED‐HEAD.

387
00:23:34,804 --> 00:23:36,738
♪

388
00:23:38,104 --> 00:23:39,938
( music playing only )

389
00:23:39,971 --> 00:23:42,638
Gon: NEXT TIME,
"AWAKENING AND POTENTIAL."

390
00:23:42,704 --> 00:23:44,304
( grunts, yells )

391
00:23:44,371 --> 00:23:46,204
DID YOU FEEL ANYTHING?

392
00:23:46,238 --> 00:23:47,971
Killua: NOPE. NOTHING.

